---
import Header from './NTNUHeader.astro';
import background from '../assets/Copilot_20260424_144616.png';
import HonestyDeclaration from './HonestyDeclaration.astro';
---
<Header/>
<div id="container">
	<img id="background" src={background.src} alt="" fetchpriority="high" />
	<main>
		<section id="introduction">
			<h1>Assignment: Card Detector</h1>

			<p>
				Welcome to the Card Detector assignment! In this task, you will develop a card detection system using computer vision techniques. 
				The goal is to identify and locate playing cards in images or video streams using an Android or iOS phone. 
			</p>
			<p>
				The assignment will use a deep learning based approach, training a convolutional neural network (CNN) to identify cards rank and suit
				as well as their location and angle.
			</p>
		</section>
		<section id="training_data">
			<h2>Training Data</h2>
			<p>
				To train your card detection model, you will need a dataset of labeled card images such as the ones shown below.
				<table>
					<thead>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr>
							<td><img src="/assets/card1.png" alt="Card 1" width="30%" /></td>
							<td><img src="/assets/card2.png" alt="Card 2" width="30%" /></td>
							<td><img src="/assets/card3.png" alt="Card 3" width="30%" /></td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>	
				</table> 
				You can create your own dataset by taking photos of playing cards in various orientations and lighting conditions, 
				or you can use an existing dataset such as the "Playing Cards Dataset" available on Kaggle.
			</p>
			<p>
				Make sure to label your images with the correct rank and suit of the cards, as well as their location and angle in the image. 
				This will be crucial for training your model effectively.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section id="honesty">
			<HonestyDeclaration />
		</section>
	</main>
</div>

<style>
	#background {
		position: fixed;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		width: 100%;
		height: 100%;
		z-index: -1;
		filter: brightness(25%);
	}

	#container {
		font-family: Inter, Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', 'Arial Nova', 'Nimbus Sans', Arial, sans-serif;
		height: 100%;
	}

	main {
		height: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	h1 {
		padding: 10px;
		font-size: 48px;
		margin-top: 0.25em;
	}

	h2 {
		padding: 10px;
		font-size: 36px;
		margin: 0 0 1em;
		font-weight: normal;
	}

	.container a, a:link, a:active, a:-webkit-any-link {
		color: #E0F7FA !important;
	}

	#links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 16px;
	}

	#links a {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		padding: 10px 12px;
		color: whitesmoke;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.2s;
	}

	#links a:hover {
		color: rgb(200, 180, 186);
	}

	#links a svg {
		height: 1em;
		margin-left: 8px;
	}

	#links a.button {
		color: white;
		background: linear-gradient(83.21deg, #3245ff 0%, #bc52ee 100%);
		box-shadow:
			inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12),
			inset 0 -2px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.24);
		border-radius: 10px;
	}

	#links a.button:hover {
		color: rgb(230, 230, 230);
		box-shadow: none;
	}

	pre {
		font-family:
			ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Source Code Pro', Menlo, Consolas, 'DejaVu Sans Mono',
			monospace;
		font-weight: normal;
		background: linear-gradient(14deg, #d83333 0%, #f041ff 100%);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 16px;
		line-height: 24px;
		letter-spacing: -0.006em;
		margin: 0;
	}

	code {
		display: inline-block;
		background:
			linear-gradient(66.77deg, #f3cddd 0%, #f5cee7 100%) padding-box,
			linear-gradient(155deg, #d83333 0%, #f041ff 18%, #f5cee7 45%) border-box;
		border-radius: 8px;
		border: 1px solid transparent;
		padding: 6px 8px;
	}

	.box {
		padding: 16px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 1);
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid white;
	}

	#news {
		position: absolute;
		bottom: 16px;
		right: 16px;
		max-width: 300px;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: background 0.2s;
		backdrop-filter: blur(50px);
	}

	#news:hover {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
	}

	@media screen and (max-height: 368px) {
		#news {
			display: none;
		}
	}

	@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
		#container {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
		}

		#hero {
			display: block;
			padding-top: 10%;
		}

		#links {
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}

		#links a.button {
			padding: 14px 18px;
		}

		#news {
			right: 16px;
			left: 16px;
			bottom: 2.5rem;
			max-width: 100%;
		}

		h1 {
			line-height: 1.5;
		}
	}
</style>
